for 700g beef
use
 - inside round cap steak a.k.a. pavé d'intérieur de ronde
try with outside skirt steak a.k.a fajita steak a.k.a. steak de hampe


combine in food processor
 - 40g dry roasted peanuts
 - 10g onion powder
 - 9g salt
 - 8g papprika
 - 5g ground ginger
 - 4g garlic powder
 - 2.5g white pepper
 - 2.5g ground allspice
 - 2.5g cayenne
process until peanuts pieces are very small
reserve 25g of the spice mixture
add to the rest
 - 1 tsp baking soda

slice beef against the grain to 1/4 inch
place in a bowl
stir in 
 - 3 tbsp peanut oil
stir spice and baking soda mixture
refrigerate for 0.5 to 12 hours
thread onto skewers
brush one side with oil
sprinkle remaining spice mix

cook on very high grill 2-3 minutes per side

in Nigeria, the cooked suya is left to rest for a few hours
and then reheated on the grill later to intensify the flavors

serve with
 - flat bread
 - tomatoes
 - raw onions
 - lettuce

source https://www.seriouseats.com/nigerian-beef-suya 
